text:
Easy way to create a drawing space, for your forehead, without green screen or transparencies. These will vary in how (or even if possible), based on program.

1) Make the background your skintone (probably a settings option). Also works, if you make the background transparent, instead of a color, but that's not always an option.

2) Use a program with drawing layers, & make the bottom layer skintone, & draw on the layer above it.

3) holo EN has artists, just ask your friends for advice.


I have tips for Atlantis, too, but don't know the best place to put them, when it's been so long since you've played Minecraft.
